- Download a qcow image (https://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/jammy/current/):

  E.g. https://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/jammy/current/jammy-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk-kvm.img


- Create a root password (https://askubuntu.com/questions/451673/default-username-password-for-ubuntu-cloud-image):
  (You need: guestfs-tools)

  ```
  virt-customize -a jammy-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk-kvm.img --root-password password:<pass>
  ```

- Grow the disk (https://gist.github.com/joseluisq/2fcf26ff1b9c59fe998b4fbfcc388342):

  ```
  qemu-img create -f qcow2 -o preallocation=metadata newdisk.qcow2 50G
  virt-resize --expand /dev/vda1 jammy-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk-kvm.img newdisk.qcow2 
  ```

- Run the image:

  ```
 ./start.sh newdisk.qcow2
  ```

- Fix boot (https://serverfault.com/a/976794):

  ```
  virt-rescue quest1-shrinked.qcow

  mkdir /mnt
  mount /dev/sda3 /mnt
  mount --bind /dev /mnt/dev
  mount --bind /proc /mnt/proc
  mount --bind /sys /mnt/sys
  chroot /mnt
  grub-install /dev/sda
  ```
